<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="312" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,760,1313,2073]" lastBlockId="23.[828,1437,190,853]" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,1313,1337]" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennae brown. Antennomere III longer than II. Pronotum with smoky stripe reaching posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[159,245,1378,1401]" captionStart="Figs 5" captionStartId="6.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[248,1334,197,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 5A–F.Dorsal and ventral surface.A–B – Hypoxys servillei sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys stysi sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys venustus sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177537/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Thoracic and abdominal pleurites and sternites with black spots (
<figureCitation box="[343,428,1410,1433]" captionStart="Figs 5" captionStartId="6.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[248,1334,197,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 5A–F.Dorsal and ventral surface.A–B – Hypoxys servillei sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys stysi sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys venustus sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177537/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
). Anterior excavation of metasternal process harboring fourth and less than half of third rostral segment (
<figureCitation box="[339,439,1474,1497]" captionStart="Figs 18" captionStartId="24.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[183,1404,198,1968]" captionTargetId="figure-13@24.[183,1404,189,1984]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figs 18A–F. Hypoxys servillei sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177561" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177561/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Fig. 18F</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[461,632,1473,1497]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[159,298,1506,1529]" captionStart="Figs 18" captionStartId="24.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[183,1404,198,1968]" captionTargetId="figure-13@24.[183,1404,189,1984]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figs 18A–F. Hypoxys servillei sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177561" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177561/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Figs 18A–D</figureCitation>
). Posterolateral angles developed, bent inwards, acuminate (
<figureCitation box="[353,452,1538,1561]" captionStart="Figs 18" captionStartId="24.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[183,1404,198,1968]" captionTargetId="figure-13@24.[183,1404,189,1984]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figs 18A–F. Hypoxys servillei sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177561" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177561/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Fig. 18A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup parallel to dorsal rim, long, almost reaching posterolateral angles, slightly concave medially; inner (proximal) part truncate, ventral angle with long digitiform process; outer (distal) part tongue-like and enlarged (
<figureCitation box="[620,748,1666,1689]" captionStart="Figs 18" captionStartId="24.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[183,1404,198,1968]" captionTargetId="figure-13@24.[183,1404,189,1984]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figs 18A–F. Hypoxys servillei sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177561" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177561/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Figs 18C,D</figureCitation>
). Paramere with two lobes; anterior lobe triangular, long, and directed to base of proctiger; lateral lobe short and rounded (
<figureCitation box="[254,383,1762,1785]" captionStart="Figs 18" captionStartId="24.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[183,1404,198,1968]" captionTargetId="figure-13@24.[183,1404,189,1984]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figs 18A–F. Hypoxys servillei sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177561" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177561/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Figs 18C,D</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with tufts of long setae along lateral excavation; posterior face bell-shaped (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 18" captionStartId="24.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[183,1404,198,1968]" captionTargetId="figure-13@24.[183,1404,189,1984]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figs 18A–F. Hypoxys servillei sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177561" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177561/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Figs 18C,D</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with expansions developed, robust, distally rounded, ventrolateral side with broad striated excavation, dorsal side with brown spot; surpassing level of posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation box="[432,536,1922,1945]" captionStart="Figs 18" captionStartId="24.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[183,1404,198,1968]" captionTargetId="figure-13@24.[183,1404,189,1984]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figs 18A–F. Hypoxys servillei sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177561" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177561/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Fig. 18B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[559,759,1921,1945]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Genital plates (
<figureCitation box="[322,423,1954,1977]" captionStart="Figs 18" captionStartId="24.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[183,1404,198,1968]" captionTargetId="figure-13@24.[183,1404,189,1984]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figs 18A–F. Hypoxys servillei sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177561" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177561/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Fig. 18E</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 posterior margin slightly concave, posterolateral angle dentiform and posteriorly directed, inner angle dentiform and projected to valvifers 9; imaginary line tangent to posterolateral angles almost reaching distal margin of valvifers 9; U-shaped excavation. Valvulae 8 visible. Apices of laterotergites 8 just passing level of apices of abdominal segment VII. Laterotergites 9 surpassing band connecting laterotergites 8; apices clearly below imaginary line tangent to apices of abdominal segment VII.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="312" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[828,1437,190,853]" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[858,1019,382,405]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Measurements</emphasis>
(n = 4; mm). Total length 16.2–18.6; head length 1.7–1.9; head width 3.1–3.2; pronotum width 10.6–11.2; abdomen width 7.8–8.5; length of antennomeres: I – 0.8–1.0; II – 1.1–1.5; III – 1.4–3.5; IV – 3.6; V – missing; scutellum length 7.3–7.5; scutellum width 5.3–5.5; pronotum length 3.1–4.8.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
